Behind the Scenes: Why Our Retinol Serum Took 2 Years to Launch?

Retinol is the superpower ingredient in skincare — but it’s also notoriously hypersensitive.

I tried using retinol myself early on. The journey? Rough. My skin broke out, peeled, and basically protested hard.

We knew if we wanted to build something people could actually use daily without fear, we couldn’t rush.

So we spent a full year traveling to fairs and scouting products internationally — learning from the best formulations out there.

That’s when we discovered a clean, oil-based retinol format that calmed the irritation but kept the power intact.

Another year of testing, tweaking, and applying it on real skin (including mine), until it finally delivered visible results — without the dreaded peeling or breakouts.

Now, our retinol serum is a bestseller — because it works with your skin, not against it.

This isn’t just a product. It’s two years of commitment, care, and a deep understanding of what clean, effective skincare really means.

✨Because when it comes to retinol, results > rush. Always.

NOT ALL DIYs ARE BAD BUT…there is always a BUT.
Day 4 of 30 Skincare Myths with Ash!
Let’s bust some common ones —
“Lemon clears pigmentation” 🍋 & “Toothpaste dries pimples” 🧴

Sounds harmless? Not quite.
Lemon can cause burns.
Toothpaste throws off your skin’s pH and damages your barrier.
Especially for Indian skin — these hacks can leave lasting damage.

💛 I personally love DIYs — with gentle ingredients like honey, curd, turmeric, and milk — but only when I’ve tested them! Perfect for a Sunday glow-up before an event, but not a replacement for real skincare.

✨ DIYs only work when your skin is healthy, hydrated, and properly cared for.
That means a good skincare routine is non-negotiable — cleanse, treat, hydrate, protect.
Without that foundation, even natural remedies can backfire.
